---
import BaseLayout from "@layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { SITE } from "@data/site";
const updated = "May 12, 2026";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms"
  description="OpenBurnBar terms of use — license, warranty disclaimer, subscription terms, acceptable use."
>
  <section class="legalpage">
    <div class="container container--narrow">
      <span class="eyebrow eyebrow--ember">Legal</span>
      <h1>Terms of use</h1>
      <p class="muted small mono">Last updated: {updated}</p>

      <p class="lead">
        OpenBurnBar is open-source software offered under the MIT License, plus an optional in-app
        subscription billed through the Apple App Store. By installing or using OpenBurnBar, you
        agree to the terms below. If you don't, please don't install the software.
      </p>

      <h2>1. License — the app</h2>
      <p>
        The OpenBurnBar source code is released under the
        <a href={`${SITE.github}/blob/main/LICENSE`} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >MIT License</a
        >. The MIT terms govern your use, modification, and distribution of the source. The
        disclaimer of warranty in the MIT License applies.
      </p>

      <h2>2. License — this website</h2>
      <p>
        Content on burnbar.ai (copy, illustrations, generated mockups) is the property of <strong
          >{SITE.entity}</strong
        >. You may quote and reference with attribution. You may not reproduce the site in full or
        use it to imply endorsement.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Subscription terms (Hosted Quota Sync)</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          The OpenBurnBar Cloud subscription (product id <code>{SITE.iapProductId}</code>) is
          offered as an in-app purchase through the Apple App Store at an intended price of US ${
            SITE.iapPriceUSD
          } per {SITE.iapPeriod}.
        </li>
        <li>
          Billing, taxes, and currency conversion are handled by Apple under the terms of the App
          Store. We do not see or store payment cards.
        </li>
        <li>
          The subscription auto-renews monthly unless canceled. Manage or cancel in <em
            >Settings → Apple ID → Subscriptions</em
          > on iPhone or iPad.
        </li>
        <li>
          Refunds are governed by Apple's standard App Store refund policy at
          <a href="https://reportaproblem.apple.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
            >reportaproblem.apple.com</a
          >.
        </li>
        <li>
          The subscription is bound to your Firebase UID via a signed Apple
          <code>appAccountToken</code> UUID and verified server-side against Apple's <em
            >getAllSubscriptionStatuses</em
          > endpoint.
        </li>
        <li>
          We may rate-limit hosted refresh and relay capacity (see the
          <a href="/pricing">pricing page</a> for current caps).
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>4. Acceptable use</h2>
      <p>
        You agree not to: (a) attempt to circumvent the entitlement model or rate limits; (b) use
        OpenBurnBar's hosted infrastructure to relay traffic that doesn't belong to you; (c)
        reverse-engineer the JWS verification or App Check chain; (d) use OpenBurnBar to violate any
        provider's terms of service for the credentials you connect.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Trust boundaries</h2>
      <p>
        OpenBurnBar reads provider data only with credentials or session material you explicitly
        provide. You are responsible for ensuring you have the right to connect any credential you
        supply, and for keeping those credentials secret. We will not knowingly process credentials
        we believe are not authorized by their issuer.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Disclaimer of warranty</h2>
      <p>
        OpenBurnBar is provided "as is" and "as available," without warranty of any kind, express or
        implied, including merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, or non-infringement.
        Cost numbers are estimates from public vendor pricing tables; we do not warrant accuracy and
        you should not rely on OpenBurnBar for accounting, tax, billing, or compliance decisions.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Limitation of liability</h2>
      <p>
        To the maximum extent permitted by law, <strong>{SITE.entity}</strong> shall not be liable for
        any indirect, incidental, consequential, special, or punitive damages arising from your use of
        OpenBurnBar — including but not limited to lost profits, business interruption, loss of data,
        or unexpected vendor charges.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Changes to these terms</h2>
      <p>
        We may update these terms as the product evolves. Material changes will be noted in the
        <a href={`${SITE.github}/blob/main/CHANGELOG.md`} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
          >project changelog</a
        >
        and reflected in the "last updated" date above.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>{SITE.entity}</strong>. <br />
        Email: <a href={`mailto:${SITE.privacyContact}`}>{SITE.privacyContact}</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legalpage {
    padding-block: var(--s-9);
  }
  .legalpage h1 {
    margin-top: var(--s-3);
    margin-bottom: var(--s-2);
  }
  .legalpage h2 {
    margin-top: var(--s-7);
    margin-bottom: var(--s-3);
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    font-variation-settings:
      "opsz" 80,
      "wght" 500;
  }
  .legalpage p,
  .legalpage ul {
    color: var(--text-base);
    max-width: 64ch;
  }
  .legalpage ul {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--s-2);
    margin: var(--s-3) 0;
    padding-left: 1.2em;
  }
  .legalpage ul li {
    list-style: disc;
    list-style-position: outside;
    padding-left: 0.4em;
  }
  .legalpage strong {
    color: var(--text-bright);
  }
  .legalpage a {
    color: var(--ember-bright);
    text-decoration: underline;
  }
  .lead {
    margin-top: var(--s-3);
    margin-bottom: var(--s-5);
  }
  .small {
    font-size: var(--t-caption);
  }
</style>
